07/08/2009
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Savka Dabcevic-Kucar, one of the most prominent politicians in Croatia's history, died Thursday (August 6th) in Zagreb at the age of 86. She headed the 1970s movement Croatian Spring. It called for greater rights for Croatia, then part of Yugoslavia, as well as democratic and economic reforms. In October 1990, she founded the Croatian People's Party (HNS) and served as its leader for three terms. (HRT, HINA, Vecernji List, Javno, Dnevnik - 06/08/09)
